data.title: Stratified squamous epithelium - Vocab, Definition, and Must Know Facts
data.meta_description: Stratified squamous epithelium is a type of tissue composed of multiple layers of flat cells that provide protection against mechanical stresses and abrasion. It lines surfaces where wear and tear are prevalent, such as the skin, mouth, and esophagus.
data.text:
Definition

Stratified squamous epithelium is a type of tissue composed of multiple layers of flat cells that provide protection against mechanical stresses and abrasion. It lines surfaces where wear and tear are prevalent, such as the skin, mouth, and esophagus.
